@node Loaders.Alpha "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

    Loader - Alpha


            This loader file is used to form a composite image from
        two different images. Unlike other similar functions, this
        allows you to load in a third image to define the intensity
        of composition for each pixel.
            The process of using the alpha channel requires loading
        in a background image, the loading of a grayscale alpha image,
        and then finally the foreground image.
            The alpha image must be a grayscale image of the exact
        same size as the foreground image. The image must also be
        compatible with the IFF image loader.

            In order to perform the composition, you must first load
        any image you wish to use as the backgroung image. Then select
        the Alpha file loader and load in the alpha grayscale image.
        Last, set the Control Panel to use Composite mode when loading
        images, and load in the foreground image.
            The Composite control panel will open. Press OK to load the
        image and perform the data composition.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Anim "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

    Loader - Anim


            This loader recognizes IFF-ANIM OP Mode 5 animations,
        produced by most Amiga animation software. You may request
        any frame of that animation so long as that frame number is
        contained in that file. This loader loads in only one frame
        of the animation.
            The Count Frames gadget will inspect the animation to
        determine the number of frames in the file. Since it is
        assumed that you may wish to load multiple frames, AdPro
        will automatically increment the intended frame number to
        load, although this may be changed while loading a new frame.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Backdrop "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Backdrop


            This loader is used to create backdrop images. These can
        include solid colored images as well as dithered and gradiated
        images. Other graphical images can then be composited or
        superimposed with other features of AdPro.

            The Color option sets the backdrop as a 24 bitplane color
        image, while the Gray option sets up an 8 bitplane grayscale
        image.
            The width and height can me modified using the W and H
        input gadgets, while colors can be modified using the R, G,
        and B color sliders.
            The Grad option sets the gradiated backdrop. Each square
        displayed on the screen represents a possible color which can
        be used in the gradiation (displayed in the upper right when
        selected). The Fill option will create one solid background
        color with no gradiation.
            The Copy button can be used to copy a color in a gradient
        fill from one corner of the backdrop to another, with the
        four boxes representing the four corners of an image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Backline "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Backline


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.BMP "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - BMP


            This loader recognizes compressed and uncompressed BMP
        files created using Windows 3.0 on MS-DOS compatible
        computers. BMP files support both 8 bitplanes and 24 bitplanes.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Clipboard "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Clipboard


            This loader recognizes graphical images stored in the
        Amiga's clipboard. Since the clipboard is shared among
        all applications, it may contain various types of data.
        This loader reads the standard graphical storage format of
        the Kickstart operating system.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.DPIIE "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - DPIIE


            This loader recognizes DPIIE files created using Deluxe
        Paint II Enhanced on MS-DOS compatible computers. DPIIE files
        support 8 bitplanes.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.DV21 "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - DV21


            This loader recognizes DV21 files created using DigiView 3.
        DV21 files support 21 bitplanes.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.FrameGrabber "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - FrameGrabber


            This loader is designed to be used with the Framegrabber
        hardware video digitizer, developed by Progressive Peripherals.
        The image may be captured either as an interlaced image or
        as two separate fields.
            To view the image being input to the Framegrabber board,
        press the View gadget from AdPro's screen. The viewed image
        may be captured by pressing the C key or by pressing the
        Digitize gadget on AdPro's loader control panel.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.GIF "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - GIF


            This loader recognizes GIF files created using most
        Macintosh and MS-DOS software packages. GIF files support
        8 bitplanes.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.HAME "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - HAME


            This loader recognizes HAME files created using the
        HAM-E external hardware display device. The HAME images
        are stored in normal 4 bitplane IFF files, however using
        special control codes, 24 bitplanes of data can be
        contained within these 4 bitplane files.
            This loader will load the HAME images into AdPro's
        24 bitplane buffer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.IFF "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - IFF


            This loader is the most widely used AdPro loader, as it
        recognizes the Amiga's standard graphics file formats. These
        formats include IFF, EHB, HAM, HAM8, SHAM, Dynamic HiRes,
        and other files that follow the IFF standard.
            The IFF standard was originally developed in conjunction
        with Electronic Arts in 1985, the year the Amiga 1000 was
        introduced. Some modes have been developed by third party
        developers.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Impulse "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Impulse


            This loader recognizes files created using Impulse's
        3D modeling software, such as Turbo Silver or Imagine.
        This includes 24 bitplane RGB8 files and 12 bitplane RGBN
        files.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.IV24 "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - IV24


            This loader requires the use of the Impact Vision 24
        graphics board and its support software libraries. The
        current IV24 image may be viewed by pressing the View
        key. While the image is being viewed, it may be digitized
        by pressing the D key. If the AdPro screen is to the front,
        the Digitize gadget is used to grab the image from the IV24
        graphics hardware.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.JPEG "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - JPEG


            This loader recognizes files stored in the JFIF storage
        format, supported by most modern 24 bitplane software
        packages. JPEG is widely used due to its impressive compression
        method, at the expense of image quality. Almost all JPEG
        images lose some quality from the original depending on
        the amount of compression used.
            The Smoothing option allows the loader to blur sections
        of the JPEG image that may have become jagged during compression
        due to the method used by JPEG.
            JPEG supports 24 bitplane images.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.MacPaint "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - MacPaint


            This loader recognizes MacPaint files created using
        MacPaint on Macintosh computers. MacPaint files support
        1 bitplane images only.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.PCX "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - PCX


            This loader recognizes PCX files created using the
        PC Paint Brush software for MS-DOS compatible computers.
        PCX images support 8 bitplane and 24 bitplane images.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Pointer "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Pointer


            This loader is capable of grabbing the image used by a
        mouse pointer produced by another program currently running
        in memory. To do this, the loader must be accessed. The desired
        pointer must then be displayed by accessing the program that
        uses them. Then, once the desired pointer is displayed, a hot
        key sequence is used to capture the image. Pressing the
        RIGHT-ALT, RIGHT-SHIFT, and BACKSPACE keys will capture the
        currently displayed mouse pointer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.QRT "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - QRT


            This loader recognizes QRT files created using the
        QRT ray tracer. These 24 bitplane images are not
        compressed.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Screen "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Screen


            This loader is used to capture a screen that is being
        displayed by another application while AdPro is running.
        The loader will open a requester listing all existing
        screens by name. Select a screen and press the Grab gadget
        to load the screen into AdPro's buffer. The Show button
        will display the screen without capturing it.
            AdPro is also capable of capturing the menu bar displayed
        by a given screen using hotkeys. To do so, select the
        loader so that it opens the requester of active screens.
        Then switch to the desired screen to capture (you may select
        the screen and then press the Show gadget if you wish).
        Next, activate the screen with the left mouse button. Then
        use the right mouse button to display the menus or menu bar.
        To capture the screen as it appears, hold down the right
        mouse button and then press the RIGHT-ALT, RIGHT-SHIFT, and
        BACKSPACE keys. After a few seconds the screen will be
        captured and loaded into AdPro's buffer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Sculpt "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Sculpt


            This loader allows AdPro to read Sculpt images.
        Unfortunately, this format does not store information about
        the size of the file or anything else. Therefor, the
        loader will request the image file sizes upon loading.
        If the correct file sizes are not used, the image will not
        be loaded properly.
            While a grayscale image is contained in one file, the
        color images are stored in three different files, one each
        for the Red, Green, and Blue separations. These files use
        the .red, .grn, and .blu endings, respectively.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Temp "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Temp


            This loader loads images stored in the temporary Undo
        buffer used by AdPro. This allows multiple images to be
        stored in the temporary buffer and reloaded using this
        loader. The images in the temporary buffer must be stored
        using the Temp saver.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Loaders.Universal "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Loaders

   Loader - Universal


            This loader recognizes most graphical formats supported
        by the various AdPro loaders. However, it relies on each
        individual loader in order to understand the actual image
        data. Using this loader may not be fully compatible with
        all images. In the event that this cannot load an image,
        and the image type is known, try using the loader specific
        to that format.
            This may also be used to attempt to identify the file
        format of a given graphical image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


