@node Operators.Apply_Map "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Apply Map


            This operator will allow AdPro to alter the color controls
        of the RAW image data. This includes all of the color map data
        altered using the Color Controls.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Blur "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Blur


            This operator allows AdPro to blur specific images in an
        image based upon how they relate to their neighboring pixels.
        Each pixel is averaged with the pixels adjacent to it in all
        directions. The Center Wight and Threshold may be modified.

            CENTER WEIGHT       Determines the amount of blur for the
                                given pixel. Lower CENTER WEIGHTS
                                increase the amount of blurring. May
                                range from 1 to 16.

            THRESHOLD           Determines how likely a pixel will
                                be affected. Lower thresholds increase
                                the likelihood a pixel will be changed.
                                May range from 0 to 255.

            PIXELS AFFECTED     Displays how many pixels will be
                                affected by the Blur operator,
                                after a TEST has been performed.

            TEST                Tests the Blur operation without
                                changing any of the image data, and
                                displays the results in the PIXELS
                                AFFECTED window.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Broadcast_Limit "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Broadcast Limit


            This operator allows AdPro to alter the IRE values of the
        image to be displayed. Some images will become distorted if
        the IRE levels are too high, so they may be modified to bring
        them within safer levels with less distortion at the expense
        of color range.

            COMPOSITE LIMIT     Sets the upper IRE value possible by
                                any given pixel.

            CHROMA LIMIT        Sets the amount of chroma to be
                                adjusted per pixel. When setting
                                luminance, the entire picture
                                darkens. When setting saturation,
                                the picture becomes greyscale.


            Two gadgets allow the Broadcast Limit operator to perform
        special functions.

            DEFAULTS            Resets the values to the default values
                                contained in the Broadcast Limit
                                operator.

            TEST                Calculates the number of pixels that
                                will be altered if the operation is
                                performed, without altering the image.


            Two cycle gadgets set other aspects of the image display
        or manipulation.

            NTSC                Modifies and enhances the output for
                                NTSC capable systems.

            PAL                 Modifies and enhances the output for
                                PAL capable systems.

            SATURATION          Allows the operator to reduce the
                                amount of color contained in any given
                                pixel.

            LUMINANCE           Allows the operator to reduce the
                                amount of brightness contained in any
                                given pixel.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Collapse "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Collapse


            This operator allows AdPro to collapse an image about an
        origin. This rotation may be set to a specific number of
        degrees, and may also be blurred. The algorithm also allows
        for a FAST mode and a HIGH QUALITY mode.

            CENTER X        Specifies the origin about the X axis,
                            measured from the left edge of the screen
                            image.

            CENTER Y        Specifies the origin about the Y axis,
                            measured from the top edge of the screen
                            image.

            RADIUS          Specifies the radius of the area to be
                            affected by the Collapse operator. This is
                            reflected by the outermost circle drawn.

            AMOUNT          Specifies the amount to collapse the image.

            BRADIUS         Specifies the percentage of the area to be
                            blurred by the Collapse operator. This is
                            reflected by the innermost circle drawn.


            This operator also includes gadgets to recenter the origin,
        or a cycle gadget to specify whether the FAST or HIGH QUALITY
        algorithm should be used.

            CENTER X        Center the origin about the X axis, at half
                            the width of the image.

            CENTER Y        Center the origin about the Y axis, at half
                            the height of the image.

            HIGH QUALITY    Set the Collapse operator to use HIGH QUALITY
                            mode, permitting higher quality images at
                            the expense of speed.

            FAST            Set the Collapse operator to use FAST mode,
                            allowing faster data calculations at the
                            expense of image quality.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Color_to_Gray "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Color to Gray


            This operator is used to convert a color image into a
        grayscale image. This includes using the average color
        weights provided by each pixel, using the standard NTSC
        color to grayscale conversion, or your own custom values.

            RED WEIGHT          Allows you to specify the amount of
                                RED to be used in calculating the
                                transformation into a grayscale image.

            GREEN WEIGHT        Allows you to specify the amount of
                                GREEN to be used in calculating the
                                transformation into a grayscale image.

            BLUE WEIGHT         Allows you to specify the amount of
                                BLUE to be used in calculating the
                                transformation into a grayscale image.

            AVERAGE WEIGHTS     Sets the weighted values of each color
                                to the average value of all of the colors,
                                giving them equal conversion into the
                                grayscale image.

            LUMINANCE WEIGHTS   Specifies that the standard NTSC color
                                to grayscale conversion is used.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Colorize "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Colorize


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Convolve "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Convolve


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Crop_Image "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Crop Image


            This operator can be used to clip a smaller region of a
        larger image and use that image as the new image. The width
        and height can be specified, along with the top left pixel
        coordinate.

            NEW WIDTH           The width of the clipped area.

            NEW HEIGHT          The height of the clipped area.

            X OFFSET            Specifies the distance, in pixels,
                                from the left edge of the screen,
                                defining the left edge of the image
                                to be clipped.

            Y OFFSET            Specifies the distance, in pixels,
                                from the top edge of the screen,
                                defining the top edge of the image
                                to be clipped.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Crop_Visual "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Crop Visual


            This operator can be used to clip a smaller region of a
        larger image and use that image as the new image. The width
        and height can be specified, along with the top left pixel
        coordinate.

            NEW WIDTH           The width of the clipped area.

            NEW HEIGHT          The height of the clipped area.

            X OFFSET            Specifies the distance, in pixels,
                                from the left edge of the screen,
                                defining the left edge of the image
                                to be clipped.

            Y OFFSET            Specifies the distance, in pixels,
                                from the top edge of the screen,
                                defining the top edge of the image
                                to be clipped.

            SNAP X              Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                                horizontally, such that the grab box
                                width must be a multiple of this value.

            SNAP Y              Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                                vertically, such that the grab box height
                                must be a multiple of this value.


            The measurement units may be displayed in English or Metric
        form. These values correspond to the above pixels, as displayed
        on the screen. The measurement units have the same fields as
        the pixel fields, with WIDTH, HEIGHT, OFFSETX, and OFFSETY.


            The Visual editor also allows other operations to be
        performed, such as in positioning the grab box. There is one
        cycle gadget for freezing the aspect ratio, and another normal
        gadget for resizing the grab box to the full size of the screen.

            KEEP ASPECT         Freezes the aspect ratio of the grab box,
                                such that any scaling of the grab box
                                will move both the width and height
                                proportionally.

            IGNORE ASPECT       Allows the grab box to be shaped in any
                                aspect ratio.

            FULL SIZE           Sets the grab box to the same size and
                                proportion of the original image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.DCTV "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - DCTV


            This operator is used to create a DCTV compatible image for
        use with the DCTV hardware adapter. In order to create a 3
        bitplane DCTV image, AdPro must be set for 8 color mode. Otherwise,
        a 4 bitplane DCTV image will be created. The image may then be
        saved using the standard IFF saver as an 8 or 16 color image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Define_Pixel_Aspect "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Define Pixel Aspect


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Deinterlace "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Deinterlace


            This operator takes and image and divides it into two
        fields of the same image, producing two images. The first
        image will contain all of the odd numbered scan lines, while
        the second image will contain all of the even numbered scan
        lines. This allows the seperate fields of a television
        image to be modified individually.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Displace_Pixel "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Displace Pixel


            This operator allows pixels to be scattered about the image.
        The Radius variable sets the radius of a circle of space which
        any given pixel can be moved in, with that pixel at the origin.
        The Probability variable sets the likelihood that any given
        pixel will be moved. The Seed variable allows AdPro to produce
        either duplicate results on various images or differing results
        on various images. If the same seed is used on the same original
        image, the image produced will be identical to others of the
        same seed. To produce a unique image from the same original
        image, use a different seed variable.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Dynamic_Range "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Dynamic Range


            This operator allows AdPro to modify an image's contrast
        of colors. The operator first scans the image for the lowest
        and highest color values used. These minimum and maximum values
        can be changed in the Dynamic Range requester that opens after
        scanning the image.
            This operator is useful to prevent banding of images due
        to highly contrasting colors, or to limit smearing of televised
        images by lowering the maximum brightness of the image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Gray_to_Color "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Gray to Color


            This operator converts a grayscale image into a color image,
        preserving the grayscale attributes of the original image, but
        storing it in a color format.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Halve "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Halve


            This operator allows an image to scale to half of its size
        without using the Scale operator. This has been designed to
        halve an image without requiring the inputs queried by the
        Scale operator, since halving the size of an image is a
        frequently used operation. Since this operator halves both
        the height and the width of the image, the resulting image
        is in fact one quarter the size of the original image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Horizontal_Flip "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Horizontal Flip


            This operator will produce a mirror image of the original,
        about the Y axis. This is similar to placing a mirror to the
        immediate right or left of the image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Intensity_Range "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Intensity Range


            This operator will remove intensity levels both at the
        most intense and least intense levels of the range of intensities.
        The 24 BIT raw data will be scanned for intensity values and
        will be displayed onscreen in the form of a histrogram. Below the
        histogram are two delimiters that may be slid horizontally to
        remove pixels of a particular intensity range, setting those
        pixels to black.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Interlace "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Interlace


            This operator will lace two images together, forming a new
        image. The odd scanlines will be composed of the first image,
        and the even scanlines will be composed of the second image.
        This can be done first by setting the raw image space size to
        that of the interlaced image, or twice either of the nonlaced
        frames. This may be done with the BACKDROP Loader. Then, use the
        Composite mode to load in the first image, and place it at the
        top half of the screen. Load in the second nonlaced image and
        place it at the bottom of the screen. Then select this operator,
        and the new interlaced image will be formed.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Kill_Temp "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Kill Temp


            This operator will remove and permenantly delete any image
        stored in AdPro's temporary buffer. These images are stored
        and recalled using the Temp loader and saver. However, any images
        in the buffer during a Kill Temp operation will no longer be
        available.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Line_Art "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Line Art


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Median_Filter "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Median Filter


            This operator will investigate every pixel of the image,
        and calculate the median value of the pixels immediately
        surrounding the current pixel. The current pixel will then
        be replaced by the median value if it deviates from the threshold
        defined in AdPro.

            THRESHOLD           Specifies the likelihodd that a pixel
                                will be replaced by a median value,
                                ranging from 0 to 255, with a value of
                                0 increasing the likelihood that the
                                median value will be used.

            TEST                Calculates the number of pixels that
                                will be altered if the operation is
                                performed, without altering the image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Negative "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Negative


            This operator produces a negative image of the data in
        memory. If the image is grayscale, the negative of each
        grayscale value will be produced. If the image is color, the
        negative of each primary color is produced.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.OpalPaint "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - OpalPaint


            This operator loads the image currently in AdPro's buffer
        into OpalPaint, allowing the use of OpalPaint to modify an
        image to be transferred back into the AdPro buffer. After the
        OpalPaint image has been modified, the new image may be
        transferred back to AdPro upon exiting OpalPaint. If you choose
        to cancel the transfer upon exiting OpalPaint, the original
        unchanged image will remain in the AdPro buffer.
            This operator requires the OpalPaint software and the
        OpalVision graphics board.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Polar_Mosaic "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Polar Mosaic


            This operator allows AdPro to rotate an image about an
        origin. This rotation may be set to a specific number of
        degrees, and may also be blurred. The algorithm also allows
        for a FAST mode and a HIGH QUALITY mode.

            CENTER X        Specifies the origin about the X axis,
                            measured from the left edge of the screen
                            image.

            CENTER Y        Specifies the origin about the Y axis,
                            measured from the top edge of the screen
                            image.

            RADIUS          Specifies the radius of the area to be
                            affected by the Rotate operator. This is
                            reflected by the outermost circle drawn.

            SLICES          Specifies the number of slices to be created
                            circularly about the origin.

            TRACKS          Specifies the number of tracks to be created
                            concentric to the origin.

            BRADIUS         Specifies the percentage of the area to be
                            blurred by the Rotate operator. This is
                            reflected by the innermost circle drawn.


            This operator also includes gadgets to recenter the origin,
        or a cycle gadget to specify whether the FAST or HIGH QUALITY
        algorithm should be used.

            CENTER X        Center the origin about the X axis, at half
                            the width of the image.

            CENTER Y        Center the origin about the Y axis, at half
                            the height of the image.

            HIGH QUALITY    Set the Rotate operator to use HIGH QUALITY
                            mode, permitting higher quality images at
                            the expense of speed.

            FAST            Set the Rotate operator to use FAST mode,
                            allowing faster data calculations at the
                            expense of image quality.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Rectangle "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Rectangle


            This operator will draw a rectangle on the current image.
        The rectangle can be filled or outlined, and may be composited
        with any existing image data.

            LEFT            Specifies the distance to the left edge
                            of the rectangle, measured from the left
                            edge of the screen.

            TOP             Specifies the distance to the top edge
                            of the rectangle, measured from the top
                            edge of the screen.

            WIDTH           Specifies the width of the rectangle to be
                            drawn.

            HEIGHT          Specifies the height of the rectangle to be
                            drawn.

            THICK           Specifies the thickness of the border of
                            the rectangle to be drawn, in pixels. A
                            value of -1 draws a filled rectangle.

            MIX             Specifies the amount of compositing to be
                            done, ranging from 0 to 100, with larger
                            values representing a larger percent of the
                            rectangle to be drawn.

            RED             The amount of RED to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.

            GREEN           The amount of GREEN to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.

            BLUE            The amount of BLUE to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Rectangle_Visual "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Rectangle Visual


            This operator will draw a rectangle on the current image.
        The rectangle can be filled or outlined, and may be composited
        with any existing image data.

            WIDTH           Specifies the width of the rectangle to be
                            drawn.

            HEIGHT          Specifies the height of the rectangle to be
                            drawn.

            OFFSET X        Specifies the distance to the left edge
                            of the rectangle, measured from the left
                            edge of the screen.

            OFFSET Y        Specifies the distance to the top edge
                            of the rectangle, measured from the top
                            edge of the screen.

            SNAP X          Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                            horizontally, such that the grab box
                            width must be a multiple of this value.

            SNAP Y          Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                            vertically, such that the grab box height
                            must be a multiple of this value.

            THICKNESS       Specifies the thickness of the border of
                            the rectangle to be drawn, in pixels. A
                            value of -1 draws a filled rectangle.


            The measurement units may be displayed in English or Metric
        form. These values correspond to the above pixels, as displayed
        on the screen. The measurement units have the same fields as
        the pixel fields, with WIDTH, HEIGHT, OFFSETX, and OFFSETY.


            MIX PCT         Specifies the amount of compositing to be
                            done, ranging from 0 to 100, with larger
                            values representing a larger percent of the
                            rectangle to be drawn.

            RED             The amount of RED to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.

            GREEN           The amount of GREEN to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.

            BLUE            The amount of BLUE to be used in defining
                            the rectangle's color.


            The Visual editor also allows other operations to be
        performed, such as in positioning the grab box. There is one
        cycle gadget for freezing the aspect ratio, and another normal
        gadget for resizing the grab box to the full size of the screen.

            KEEP ASPECT         Freezes the aspect ratio of the grab box,
                                such that any scaling of the grab box
                                will move both the width and height
                                proportionally.

            IGNORE ASPECT       Allows the grab box to be shaped in any
                                aspect ratio.

            FULL SIZE           Sets the grab box to the same size and
                                proportion of the original image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Remove_Isolated_Pixels "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Remove Isolated Pixels


            This operator will remove stray pixels from the image in
        the current buffer. This is done by scanning the neighboring
        images to see if they are all the same backgroung color. If
        the are, yet the current pixel is a different color, then it
        will be removed and replaced by the surrounding colors.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Rendered_to_RAW "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Rendered to RAW


            This operator allows the image in the rendered image buffer
        to be copied into the RAW image buffer. The RAW image buffer is
        used as a basis for all operations, while the Rendered image
        buffer is the ouput of any of AdPro's operations. This allows
        AdPro to support rendered images in some operators and savers
        that only support the RAW image buffer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Roll "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Roll


            This operator will roll the image in a given direction.
        The roll will slide the image a specified number of pixels,
        and is capable of sliding it off screen or wrapping it around.
        This operator is similar to the roll found on television sets
        that are not held in sync, however this operator only produces
        one frame.

            PIXELS              The number of pixels to move the image.

            ROLL DIRECTION      The direction, either horizontal,
                                vertical, or diagonal, to move the
                                image.

            WRAP                Specifies that the image is to be
                                wrapped around the opposite edge of
                                the screen.

            NO WRAP             Specifies that the image is to disappear
                                off the edge of the screen.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Rotate "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Rotate


            This operator allows AdPro to rotate an image about an
        origin. This rotation may be set to a specific number of
        degrees, and may also be blurred. The algorithm also allows
        for a FAST mode and a HIGH QUALITY mode.

            CENTER X        Specifies the origin about the X axis,
                            measured from the left edge of the screen
                            image.

            CENTER Y        Specifies the origin about the Y axis,
                            measured from the top edge of the screen
                            image.

            RADIUS          Specifies the radius of the area to be
                            affected by the Rotate operator. This is
                            reflected by the outermost circle drawn.

            AMOUNT          Specifies the amount in degrees to spin
                            the image.

            BRADIUS         Specifies the percentage of the area to be
                            blurred by the Rotate operator. This is
                            reflected by the innermost circle drawn.


            This operator also includes gadgets to recenter the origin,
        or a cycle gadget to specify whether the FAST or HIGH QUALITY
        algorithm should be used.

            CENTER X        Center the origin about the X axis, at half
                            the width of the image.

            CENTER Y        Center the origin about the Y axis, at half
                            the height of the image.

            HIGH QUALITY    Set the Rotate operator to use HIGH QUALITY
                            mode, permitting higher quality images at
                            the expense of speed.

            FAST            Set the Rotate operator to use FAST mode,
                            allowing faster data calculations at the
                            expense of image quality.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Saturation "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Saturation


            This operator allows AdPro to alter the percent of color
        saturation in an image. The amount of saturation can be
        specified along with the method of calculating the saturation.

            PERCENT         The percentage can vary between -100
                            and 100 percent using a slider gadget.

            YUV             The Luminance values of each pixel is used
                            as the base of the saturation.

            HSV             The value of each pixel is used as the
                            base of the saturation.

            HLS             The Lightness values of each pixel is used
                            as the base of the saturation.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Scale "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Scale


            This operator is used to change the size of an image
        without removing the overall look of the image. Some pixels
        may be lost when reducing an image, and pixels may be added
        when enlarging an image. This operator affects the RAW image
        data.

            WIDTH               Specifies the number of pixels in the
                                width of the scaled image.

            HEIGHT              Specifies the number of pixels in the
                                height of the scaled image.

            PIXEL ASPECT        Displays the aspect ratio of the scaled
                                image as compared to the original image.


            The image can also be scaled by using the sliders, to
        specify the percentage of scaling for the image as opposed
        to the new size of the scaled image.

            WIDTH               Specifies the percentage of change in
                                the scaled image about its width.

            HEIGHT              Specifies the percentage of change in
                                the scaled image about its height.


            The last cycle gadget defines whether AdPro will scale the
        image to be larger or smaller than the original image.

            SWITCH TO ENLARGE   Cycling this gadget sets it to enlarge
                                the current image.

            SWITCH TO REDUCE    Cycling this gadget sets it to reduce
                                the current image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Simulate_Print "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Simulate Print


            This operator simulates printing an image by rendering the
        image into AdPro's buffer. All operations that would be performed
        on the printed image are performed on the rendered image. This
        allows you to see what an image may look like when dithered by
        a printer.


            DITHER          Numerous dithering methods may be used,
                            including HALFTONE, ORDERED, VERTICAL LINE,
                            HORIZONTAL LINE, FWD DIAGONAL LINE,
                            BWD DIAGONAL LINE, FWD BRICK, and BWD BRICK.
                            These are set using a cycle gadget.

            SIZE            This sets the size of the dithering area,
                            ranging from 2 to 16, using a cycle gadget.


            @{"     " link Savers.PrefPrinter} PrefPrinter

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Spin "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Spin


            This operator allows a circular section of an image to be
        rotated about an origin. This rotation may be set to a specific
        number of degrees, and may also be blurred. The algorithm also
        allows for a FAST mode and a HIGH QUALITY mode.

            CENTER X        Specifies the origin about the X axis,
                            measured from the left edge of the screen
                            image.

            CENTER Y        Specifies the origin about the Y axis,
                            measured from the top edge of the screen
                            image.

            RADIUS          Specifies the radius of the area to be
                            affected by the Spin operator. This is
                            reflected by the outermost circle drawn.

            AMOUNT          Specifies the amount in degrees to spin
                            the image.

            BRADIUS         Specifies the percentage of the area to be
                            blurred by the Spin operator. This is
                            reflected by the innermost circle drawn.


            This operator also includes gadgets to recenter the origin,
        or a cycle gadget to specify whether the FAST or HIGH QUALITY
        algorithm should be used.

            CENTER X        Center the origin about the X axis, at half
                            the width of the image.

            CENTER Y        Center the origin about the Y axis, at half
                            the height of the image.

            HIGH QUALITY    Set the Spin operator to use HIGH QUALITY
                            mode, permitting higher quality images at
                            the expense of speed.

            FAST            Set the Spin operator to use FAST mode,
                            allowing faster data calculations at the
                            expense of image quality.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Text_Visual "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Text Visual


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Tile "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Tile


            This operator allows an image to be tiled repeatedly about
        the screen. The tiles may be displayed in a grid outlay, or they
        may be skewed horizontally or vertically. Skewing the grid will
        change the alignment from row to row or column to column.

            After selecting the image to be tiled, you may alter the
        placement or size of the image with the fields presented.

            LEFT        The position of the first tile from the left of
                        the screen border.

            TOP         The position of the first tile from the top of
                        the screen border.

            WIDTH       The width of a tile.

            HEIGHT      The height of a tile.

            SKEW        The number of pixels to displace the image from
                        row to row or column to column. To disable
                        skewing, set this to 0.


            Skewing can be toggled between two different modes using
        the cycle gadget in the operator window. Two skew modes are
        currently supported.

            VERTICAL SKEW       Sets the tiled mode to allow the image
                                to appear skewed in vertical columns.

            HORIZONTAL SKEW     Sets the tiled mode to allow the image
                                to appear skewed in horizontal rows.


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Tile_Visual "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Tile Visual


            This operator allows an image to be tiled repeatedly about
        the screen. The tiles may be displayed in a grid outlay, or they
        may be skewed horizontally or vertically. Skewing the grid will
        change the alignment from row to row or column to column.

            After selecting the image to be tiled, you may alter the
        placement or size of the image with the fields presented.

            WIDTH               The width of a tile.

            HEIGHT              The height of a tile.

            OFFSETX             The position of the first tile from the
                                left of the screen border.

            OFFSETY             The position of the first tile from the
                                top of the screen border.

            SNAP X              Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                                horizontally, such that the grab box
                                width must be a multiple of this value.

            SNAP Y              Specifies the unit size of the grab box,
                                vertically, such that the grab box height
                                must be a multiple of this value.


            The measurement units may be displayed in English or Metric
        form. These values correspond to the above pixels, as displayed
        on the screen. The measurement units have the same fields as
        the pixel fields, with WIDTH, HEIGHT, OFFSETX, and OFFSETY.


            Skewing can be toggled between two different modes using
        the cycle gadget in the operator window. Two skew modes are
        currently supported.

            VERTICAL SKEW       Sets the tiled mode to allow the image
                                to appear skewed in vertical columns.

            HORIZONTAL SKEW     Sets the tiled mode to allow the image
                                to appear skewed in horizontal rows.

            SKEW OFFSET         The number of pixels to displace the
                                image from row to row or column to
                                column. To disable skewing, set this to 0.


            The Visual editor also allows other operations to be
        performed, such as in positioning the grab box. There is one
        cycle gadget for freezing the aspect ratio, and another normal
        gadget for resizing the grab box to the full size of the screen.

            KEEP ASPECT         Freezes the aspect ratio of the grab box,
                                such that any scaling of the grab box
                                will move both the width and height
                                proportionally.

            IGNORE ASPECT       Allows the grab box to be shaped in any
                                aspect ratio.

            FULL SIZE           Sets the grab box to the same size and
                                proportion of the original image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.TPort_Controller "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Transport Controller


            This operator will allow the Transport Controller hardware
        device to record the image currently rendered in AdPro's buffer.
        Since the Transport Controller is not included with AdPro, or
        sold by ASDG, the included software sports it own interface
        which is not fully supported by AdPro.
            If the hardware is installed and operating correctly, this
        Operator will allow the Transport Controller to record the image
        currently rendered in AdPro's buffer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Twirl "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Twirl


            This operator allows a circular section of an image to be
        rotated about an origin. This rotation may be set to a specific
        number of degrees, and may also be blurred. The algorithm also
        allows for a FAST mode and a HIGH QUALITY mode.

            CENTER X        Specifies the origin about the X axis,
                            measured from the left edge of the screen
                            image.

            CENTER Y        Specifies the origin about the Y axis,
                            measured from the top edge of the screen
                            image.

            RADIUS          Specifies the radius of the area to be
                            affected by the Twirl operator. This is
                            reflected by the outermost circle drawn.

            AMOUNT          Specifies the amount in degrees to twirl
                            the image. This is reflected by a small
                            arc between the origin and along the
                            radius, drawn as a dashed line.

            BRADIUS         Specifies the percentage of the area to be
                            blurred by the Twirl operator. This is
                            reflected by the innermost circle drawn.


            This operator also includes gadgets to recenter the origin,
        or a cycle gadget to specify whether the FAST or HIGH QUALITY
        algorithm should be used.

            CENTER X        Center the origin about the X axis, at half
                            the width of the image.

            CENTER Y        Center the origin about the Y axis, at half
                            the height of the image.

            HIGH QUALITY    Set the Twirl operator to use HIGH QUALITY
                            mode, permitting higher quality images at
                            the expense of speed.

            FAST            Set the Twirl operator to use FAST mode,
                            allowing faster data calculations at the
                            expense of image quality.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Operators.Vertical_Flip "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Operators

   Operator - Vertical Flip


            This operator will produce a mirror image of the original,
        about the X axis. This is similar to placing a mirror to the
        immediate top or bottom of the image.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


