+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Clipboard "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Clipboard


            This saver will store a graphical image into the Amiga's
        clipboard device. This allows graphical images to be shared
        between various programs that support the clipboard, including
        many programs included in your Workbench disk.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.DPIIE "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - DPIIE


            This saver allows you to save images in a format readable
        by Deluxe Paint II Enhanced on MS-DOS compatible computers,
        along with all other programs that support this format. The
        DPIIE saver supports anywhere from 1 bitplane to 8 bitplane
        images.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.FC24 "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - FC24


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.FrameGrabber "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - FrameGrabber


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.GIF "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - GIF


            This saver will save graphical images in the GIF image
        format. Some images, such as those rendered in HAM, HAM8,
        or EHB mode, cannot be stored as GIF images. These images
        must therefor be converted to a standard 8 bitplane image
        or something similar. The GIF format is usable by numerous
        MS-DOS and Macintosh software packages, as well as UNIX
        and other systems. GIF is a very widely used image format.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.HAME "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - HAME


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Harlequin "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Harlequin


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.IFF "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - IFF


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Impulse "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Impulse


            This saver will save an image in either the RGBN 12 bitplane
        format or the RGB8 24 bitplane format. The Impulse format is
        primarily used by Impulse's 3D modeling packages, such as Turbo
        Silver or Imagine.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.IV24 "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - IV24


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.JPEG "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - JPEG


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.OpalVision "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - OpalVision


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.PCX "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - PCX


            This saver will store the current image in PCX format,
        readable by PC Paint Brush and other compatible software
        packages. This file format cannot be used to render HAM,
        HAM8, or EHB images from AdPro. Such images must therefor
        be converted to an 8 bitplane, 24 bitplane, or a similar
        format.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.PostScript "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - PostScript


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.PrefPrinter "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - PrefPrinter


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.QRT "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - QRT


            This saver will store the current image in the QRT file
        format. This 24 bitplane image is used by the QRT ray tracer
        and other compatible software packages.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Resolver "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Resolver


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Sculpt "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Sculpt


            This saver will store the current image in the Sculpt file
        format, requiring three separate files for the red, green, and
        blue components. It is suggested that the .red, .grn, and .blu
        file extensions be used when saving the file components.
            Since the Sculpt format does not store the size of the image,
        the user must keep track of the image sizes. It is suggested that
        the user include the file size in the name of the file or in
        its comment field.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Separate "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Separate


@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Savers.Temp "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.Savers

   Saver - Temp


            This saver is used to store the current image in the
        temporary buffer. This allows the image to be modified, while
        allowing it to be reloaded in the event it is needed once again.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


