+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.ADPRO_DISPLAY "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - ADPRO_DISPLAY


            This command will bring the currently rendered image in
        AdPro's buffer to the front of all screens, if available.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.ADPRO_EXIT "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - ADPRO_EXIT


            This command will exit AdPro and close the AdPro message
        port with the current ARexx script.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.ADPRO_TO_BACK "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - ADPRO_TO_BACK


            This command brings the AdPro control panel to the back
        of all other screens.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.ADPRO_TO_FRONT "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - ADPRO_TO_FRONT


            This command brings the AdPro control panel to the front
        of all other screens.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.ADPRO_UNDISPLAY "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - ADPRO_UNDISPLAY


            This command will bring the currently rendered image in
        AdPro's buffer to the back of all screens.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.BLUE "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - BLUE


            Without any arguments, this reports the current Blue
        setting. Otherwise, a value in the range of -50 to 50 may
        be assigned by specifying that value after this command.
        Any negative values must be delimited by quotation marks.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.BRIGHTNESS "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - BRIGHTNESS


            Without any arguments, this reports the current Brightness
        setting. Otherwise, a value in the range of -50 to 50 may
        be assigned by specifying that value after this command.
        Any negative values must be delimited by quotation marks.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.CONTRAST "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - CONTRAST


            Without any arguments, this reports the current Contrast
        setting. Otherwise, a value in the range of -50 to 50 may
        be assigned by specifying that value after this command.
        Any negative values must be delimited by quotation marks.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.CURRENT_MEM_SIZE "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - CURRENT_MEM_SIZE


            This command reports the amount of memory being used by
        AdPro.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.DITHER "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - DITHER


            This command is used to return the currently selected
        dither method used. The dither method may be changed to
        one of 9 presets be specifying a value of 0 to 8, each
        corresponding to a different method.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.EXECUTE "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - EXECUTE


            This command allows a script to render the data in AdPro's
        image buffer.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.GAMMA "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - GAMMA


            Without any arguments, this reports the current Gamma
        setting. Otherwise, a value in the range of 0 to 100 may
        be assigned by specifying that value after this command.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node ARexx.GCR "Art Department Professional"
@toc Software.AdPro.ARexx

   ARexx - GCR

@endnode
